{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773482641846,"sessionID":"ses_314328759ffeSwO8I1laVGgGu4","part":{"id":"prt_cebcd869f001cSMR4h7vm8JhIO","sessionID":"ses_314328759ffeSwO8I1laVGgGu4","messageID":"msg_cebcd78db001y9KgJMG5H644Pv","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01HH6dzWbRKRUgHp9Mdwqyr3","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wishlist-promote/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/wishlist-promote/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n2: \n3: This file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\n4: If you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n9: \n10: These are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n11: \n12: ### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n13: \n14: ```\n15: # CORRECT — runs local source directly\n16: bun dev <command> [args...]\n17: \n18: # WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\n19: wombo <command> [args...]\n20: ```\n21: \n22: **Why:** wombo is dogfooded — we develop it using itself. The global binary is a\n23: snapshot from the last release. If you use it, you're testing old code, not your\n24: changes. `bun dev` runs `bun src/index.ts` which executes the current working tree.\n25: \n26: **Examples:**\n27: ```sh\n28: bun dev help\n29: bun dev tasks list\n30: bun dev tasks add my-feat \"My Feature\" --priority high\n31: bun dev launch --dry-run --all-ready\n32: bun dev init --force\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### 2. Never publish to npm\n36: \n37: Distribution is GitHub-only. Users install via:\n38: ```sh\n39: bun install -g github:fulgidus/wombo\n40: ```\n41: Do not add `publishConfig`, do not run `npm publish`, do not add `.npmrc`.\n42: \n43: ### 3. Keep bun.lock committed\n44: \n45: The lockfile is committed for reproducible installs from GitHub. Always commit\n46: `bun.lock` after adding/removing/updating dependencies.\n47: \n48: ### 4. Do not commit user artifacts\n49: \n50: All wombo-combo user artifacts live under `.wombo-combo/` (config, tasks, archive,\n51: state, logs, history). This directory is gitignored.\n52: \n53: The template at `src/templates/tasks.yml` is the canonical source for the task\n54: file schema. The root `.wombo-combo/` dir is for local development only.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Project structure\n59: \n60: ```\n61: wombo/\n62:   package.json              # name: wombo-combo, version in sync with git tags\n63:   src/\n64:     index.ts                # CLI entry point, arg parsing, command routing\n65:     config.ts               # WomboConfig type, defaults, loader, validator\n66:     commands/\n67:       init.ts               # Interactive guided setup (Prompter class)\n68:       launch.ts             # Launch a wave of agents\n69:       resume.ts             # Resume a stopped wave\n70:       status.ts             # Show wave status\n71:       verify.ts             # Build verification\n72:       merge.ts              # Merge verified branches\n73:       retry.ts              # Retry a failed agent\n74:       cleanup.ts            # Remove worktrees and sessions\n75:       tasks/\n76:         list.ts, add.ts, set-status.ts, check.ts, archive.ts, show.ts\n77:     lib/\n78:       tasks.ts              # Task file I/O, types, ensureTasksFile guard\n79:       state.ts              # Wave state persistence\n80:       prompt.ts             # Agent prompt generation\n81:       launcher.ts           # Process spawning\n82:       monitor.ts            # ProcessMonitor\n83:       worktree.ts           # Git worktree management\n84:       merger.ts             # Git merge operations\n85:       verifier.ts           # Build verification logic\n86:       ui.ts                 # Console dashboard\n87:       tui.ts                # neo-blessed TUI\n88:     templates/\n89:       tasks.yml             # Template with full schema docs\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## User-facing file layout\n93: \n94: All wombo-combo files live under `.wombo-combo/`:\n95: \n96: ```\n97: .wombo-combo/\n98:   config.json     # Project configuration (replaces wombo.json)\n99:   tasks.yml       # Active tasks (replaces .features.yml)\n100:   archive.yml     # Completed/cancelled tasks\n101:   state.json      # Wave state\n102:   logs/           # Agent log files\n103:   history/        # Wave history records\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Coding conventions\n107: \n108: - **Runtime:** Bun (not Node). Use Bun APIs where available (`Bun.file()`,\n109:   `Bun.spawn()`, etc.), fall back to Node stdlib when Bun doesn't have a\n110:   direct equivalent.\n111: - **Language:** TypeScript, strict mode. Run `bun run typecheck` to verify.\n112: - **Modules:** ESM only (`\"type\": \"module\"` in package.json). Use `.js`\n113:   extensions in import paths (TypeScript resolves them to `.ts` at runtime in Bun).\n114: - **No external CLI frameworks.** Arg parsing is hand-rolled in `index.ts`.\n115:   This is intentional — it keeps the dependency tree minimal and gives full\n116:   control for agent-readiness features (schema introspection, etc.).\n117: - **YAML library:** `yaml` (v2). Use `YAML.parse()` / `YAML.stringify()`.\n118: - **No npm registry dependencies** for core functionality. `neo-blessed` is\n119:   the only large dependency (TUI). Keep it that way.\n120: \n121: ## Testing and verification\n122: \n123: ```sh\n124: # Type check (no emit)\n125: bun run typecheck\n126: \n127: # Build (outputs to dist/)\n128: bun run build\n129: \n130: # Run any command via dev\n131: bun dev help\n132: bun dev tasks check\n133: ```\n134: \n135: There is no test suite yet. When adding tests, use Bun's built-in test runner\n136: (`bun test`).\n137: \n138: ## Known quirks\n139: \n140: - **Bun readline + piped stdin:** `rl.question()` silently fails after readline\n141:   emits `close`. The `Prompter` class in `src/commands/init.ts` works around\n142:   this using `rl[Symbol.asyncIterator]()` with `process.stdout.write()`.\n143: - **YAML null vs empty array:** `yaml` parses `tasks:` (no items) as `null`,\n144:   not `[]`. `loadTasks()` normalizes this: `parsed.tasks ?? parsed.features ?? null`.\n145: - **`import.meta.dir`:** Gives the directory of the current source file in Bun.\n146:   Used in `src/lib/tasks.ts` to resolve the template path.\n147: \n148: ## Feature backlog\n149: \n150: The active backlog lives in `.wombo-combo/tasks.yml` (local, gitignored). Use\n151: `bun dev tasks list` to see it. The canonical template is at\n152: `src/templates/tasks.yml`.\n153: \n154: ## Making changes\n155: \n156: 1. **Check the backlog:** `bun dev tasks list`\n157: 2. **Pick a feature/subtask:** `bun dev tasks show <id>`\n158: 3. **Mark it in-progress:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> in_progress`\n159: 4. **Implement the change**\n160: 5. **Typecheck:** `bun run typecheck`\n161: 6. **Build:** `bun run build`\n162: 7. **Test manually:** `bun dev <relevant-command>`\n163: 8. **Mark done:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> done`\n164: 9. **Commit** with a conventional commit message referencing the feature ID\n165: \n166: ## Version and release\n167: \n168: - Current version is in `package.json` → `\"version\"` field.\n169: - Git tags must match: tag `v0.1.0` ↔ `\"version\": \"0.1.0\"`.\n170: - **When creating a git tag, ALWAYS update `package.json` `\"version\"` first,\n171:   commit the bump, then tag that commit.** Never tag without bumping the\n172:   version — they must stay in sync.\n173: - Release workflow (when implemented) triggers on `v*` tag push to main.\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","title":"AGENTS.md","metadata":{"preview":"# AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n\nThis file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\nIf you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n\n---\n\n## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n\nThese are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n\n### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n\n```\n# CORRECT — runs local source directly\nbun dev <command> [args...]\n\n# WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\nwombo <command> [args...]\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773482641836,"end":1773482641844}}}}
