{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482980342,"sessionID":"ses_314328759ffeSwO8I1laVGgGu4","part":{"id":"prt_cebd290db001M6VEC1wUD8tnZo","sessionID":"ses_314328759ffeSwO8I1laVGgGu4","messageID":"msg_cebd28aa7001iZkVELa1R0dF3W","type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented across 3 commits:\n\n## Completed Work\n\n### Commit 1: `feat(wishlist-promote): add WishlistPicker TUI view`\n- **`src/lib/tui-wishlist.ts`** — New 392-line blessed-based TUI view for browsing wishlist items\n  - Two-pane layout: item list (left) + detail view (right)\n  - Keybindings: **E** (promote to errand), **G** (promote to genesis), **D** (delete), **Esc** (back), **Q** (quit)\n  - Exports `WishlistPicker` class, `WishlistAction` type, and `WishlistPickerOptions` interface\n  - Follows existing TUI patterns (QuestPicker, TaskBrowser)\n\n### Commit 2: `feat(wishlist-promote): add W key and wishlist action to QuestPicker`\n- **`src/lib/tui-quest-picker.ts`** — Added:\n  - `| { type: \"wishlist\" }` variant to `QuestPickerAction` type\n  - `onWishlist?: () => void` callback to `QuestPickerOptions`\n  - **W** key binding → `triggerWishlist()` method\n  - **W wishlist** hint in the status bar\n\n### Commit 3: `feat(wishlist-promote): wire wishlist flow into TUI main loop`\n- **`src/commands/tui.ts`** — Added:\n  - `handleWishlistFlow()` — orchestrates the wishlist view, dispatches to errand/genesis flows with pre-filled text\n  - `showWishlistPicker()` — Promise-based wrapper for the WishlistPicker\n  - `maybeDeleteWishlistItem()` — post-promotion readline prompt asking `Delete wishlist item? [y/N]`\n  - `handleErrandFlow()` and `handleGenesisFlow()` now accept optional `prefill?: string` parameter that skips the readline prompt\n  - Main loop handles `questAction.type === \"wishlist\"` to enter the flow","time":{"start":1773482980341,"end":1773482980341}}}
